item.title: CVE-2019-3710|2024-08-04T19:19:17.923Z -- dell%20emc -- dell%20emc%20networking%20os10
item.description: Dell EMC Networking OS10 versions prior to 10.4.3 contain a cryptographic key vulnerability due to an underlying application using undocumented, pre-installed X.509v3 key/certificate pairs. An unauthenticated remote attacker with the knowledge of the default keys may potentially be able to intercept communications or operate the system with elevated privileges.
